   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n31:   - *Verify:* `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n32:   - *Test:* Assert class constant equals expected value\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T005** Implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` method\n35:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n36:   - *Verify:* POSTs JSON payload to base URL with session header\n37:   - *Test:* Mock HTTP, verify POST request format and headers\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T006** Implement `close()` method\n40:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n41:   - *Verify:* Closes HTTP session\n42:   - *Test:* Call close, verify session closed\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T007** Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n45:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n46:   - *Verify:* Exports `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n47:   - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T008** Add unit tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n50:   - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n51:   - *Verify:* Constructor, URL construction, invoke, close methods tested\n52:   - *Test:* pytest runs successfully\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient (T009-T019)\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T009** Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n59:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n60:   - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeClient`\n61:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T010** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` with router URL validation\n64:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n65:   - *Verify:* Accepts `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`; validates router_url from arg or ROUTER_URL env var\n66:   - *Test:* Instantiate with valid router_url; test ValueError when missing\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T011** Implement session bootstrap via GET request\n69:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n70:   - *Verify:* When session_id not provided, GET invocation URL and extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n71:   - *Test:* Mock GET response with session header; test ValueError when header missing\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T012** Implement reuse of provided session_id (skip bootstrap)\n74:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n75:   - *Verify:* When session_id provided, use it directly without bootstrap\n76:   - *Test:* Instantiate with session_id, verify no bootstrap GET made\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T013** Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n79:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n80:   - *Verify:* Creates AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient instance with correct params\n81:   - *Test:* Verify dp_client is set after init\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T014** Implement context manager `__enter__` and `__exit__`\n84:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n85:   - *Verify:* `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `close()`\n86:   - *Test:* Use client in `with` block, verify close called on exit\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T015** Implement `invoke(payload, timeout)` method\n89:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n90:   - *Verify:* Delegates to dp_client.invoke, raises ValueError if session_id not initialized\n91:   - *Test:* Call invoke with valid session; call with None session_id\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T016** Implement default timeout handling in invoke\n94:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n95:   - *Verify:* When timeout=None, uses (connect_timeout, self.timeout) tuple\n96:   - *Test:* Mock request, verify timeout tuple\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T017** Implement custom timeout in invoke\n99:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n100:   - *Verify:* When timeout is provided, uses provided value\n101:   - *Test:* Invoke with timeout=60, verify timeout passed correctly\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T018** Implement `close()` method\n104:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n105:   - *Verify:* Closes data plane client and HTTP session\n106:   - *Test:* Call close, verify resources cleaned up\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T019** Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to import from agent_runtime.py\n109:   - *File:* `agentcube/__init__.py`\n110:   - *Verify:* `from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient` in __all__\n111:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ### Phase 3: Integration Tests & Examples (T020-T023)\n116: \n117: - [ ] **T020** Write unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n118:   - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n119:   - *Verify:* Constructor, context manager, bootstrap, invoke tested\n120:   - *Test:* pytest runs successfully\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T021** Create example usage script\n123:   - *File:* `examples/agent_runtime_example.py`\n124:   - *Verify:* Demonstrates AgentRuntimeClient usage patterns\n125:   - *Test:* Script runs without syntax errors\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T022** Run full package import test\n128:   - *Verify:* All exports work correctly\n129:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T023** Run linter/typecheck on new code\n132:   - *Verify:* No linting errors\n133:   - *Test:* ruff/ruff check and mypy pass\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Dependencies\n138: \n139: | Task | Depends On |\n140: |------|------------|\n141: | T002 | T001 |\n142: | T003 | T002 |\n143: | T004 | T001 |\n144: | T005 | T003, T004 |\n145: | T006 | T001 |\n146: | T007 | T001, T005 |\n147: | T008 | T001-T007 |\n148: | T010 | T009 |\n149: | T011 | T010, (T001-T007 for dp_client) |\n150: | T012 | T010 |\n151: | T013 | T011 |\n152: | T014 | T013, T018 |\n153: | T015 | T013 |\n154: | T016 | T015 |\n155: | T017 | T015 |\n156: | T018 | T013 |\n157: | T019 | T009, T010 |\n158: | T020 | T009-T019 |\n159: | T021 | T009-T019 |\n160: | T022 | T007, T019 |\n161: | T023 | T001-T022 |\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Verification Checklist\n166: \n167: - [ ] AC001: AgentRuntimeClient constructs with proper defaults (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout)\n168: - [ ] AC002: AgentRuntimeClient creates session via GET when session_id not provided\n169: - [ ] AC003: AgentRuntimeClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n170: - [ ] AC004: AgentRuntimeClient handles missing session header during bootstrap with ValueError\n171: - [ ] AC005: AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n172: - [ ] AC006: invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy\n173: - [ ] AC007: invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload\n174: - [ ] AC008: invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header\n175: - [ ] AC009: invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None\n176: - [ ] AC010: invoke() uses custom timeout when provided\n177: - [ ] AC011: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n178: - [ ] AC012: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant\n179: - [ ] AC013: close() closes the requests.Session\n180: - [ ] AC014: Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## References\n185: \n186: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n187: - Design: `python-sdk/design.md` (AgentRuntimeClient sections)\n188: - Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n189: - Related: AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient implementation)\n\n(End of file - total 189 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (T001-T008)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n- [ ] **T002** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneCl