{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870153865,"sessionID":"ses_285e42f65ffeotFIr0rUUJXqPp","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1c106f001KhVb3joOBOq4ZL","messageID":"msg_d7a1c030a001fE2S5yTte7fYu3","sessionID":"ses_285e42f65ffeotFIr0rUUJXqPp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ab16c1d2f33a4c9fb83e5c58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-028\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: Building upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n20: 1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)\n21: 2. Invoke tools via the Agent Runtime data plane with JSON payloads\n22: 3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Requirements\n27: \n28: ### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n29: \n30: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or bootstraps a new session via GET on the invocation endpoint, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n33: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n34: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n35: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`, which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Router URL required\n38: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n39: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n40: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Constructor parameters with defaults\n43: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n44: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL set `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `verbose=False`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### AR-028-002: Session bootstrapping\n50: \n51: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL.\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Bootstrap session id\n54: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n55: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n56: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n57: - **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Reuse existing session_id\n60: - **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to constructor\n61: - **WHEN** initialization runs\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL skip session bootstrapping and use the provided session_id directly\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### AR-028-003: Invoke method\n67: \n68: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` method that POSTs JSON payloads to the data plane with session header.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — Invoke without session\n71: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy (None or empty)\n72: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` is called\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Invoke with payload\n76: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n77: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}, timeout=None)` is called\n78: - **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}` with JSON body `{\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}`\n79: - **AND** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n80: - **AND** return the response from the data plane\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-C — Invoke timeout tuple\n83: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n84: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n85: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-D — Invoke with custom timeout\n88: - **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n89: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n90: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `60` seconds\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ### AR-028-004: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n95: \n96: The `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Base URL from router components\n99: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`\n100: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n101: - **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Explicit base URL\n104: - **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n105: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n106: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ### AR-028-005: Session Header\n111: \n112: All data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Session header on requests\n115: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n116: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n117: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Session header constant\n120: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n121: - **WHEN** inspected\n122: - **THEN** it SHALL have class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ### AR-028-006: Close method\n127: \n128: The system SHALL provide a `close` method to clean up resources.\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Close releases resources\n131: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has an active session\n132: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n133: - **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Non-Requirements\n138: \n139: The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n140: - Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n141: - WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n142: - Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n143: - Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n144: - File operations directly on AgentRuntimeClient (different use case)\n145: - Tool discovery endpoints (list_tools, get_tool_schema) - not in base spec\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Dependencies\n150: \n151: | Dependency | Description |\n152: |------------|-------------|\n153: | AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n154: | python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n155: | python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification with AgentRuntimeClient requirements |\n156: | router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## Acceptance Criteria\n161: \n162: | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n163: |----|-----------|---------------------|\n164: | AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout) | Unit test |\n165: | AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url missing | Unit test |\n166: | AC-003 | Context manager properly closes resources | Integration test |\n167: | AC-004 | Bootstrap session id via GET reads x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n168: | AC-005 | Missing session header during bootstrap raises ValueError | Unit test with mock |\n169: | AC-006 | Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap | Unit test with mock |\n170: | AC-007 | invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy | Unit test |\n171: | AC-008 | invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload | Unit test with mock |\n172: | AC-009 | invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n173: | AC-010 | invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None | Unit test with mock |\n174: | AC-011 | invoke() uses custom timeout when provided | Unit test with mock |\n175: | AC-012 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components | Unit test |\n176: | AC-013 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant | Unit test |\n177: | AC-014 | close() closes the requests.Session | Unit test with mock |\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Test Strategy\n182: \n183: 1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n184: 2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n185: 3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## Implementation Notes\n190: \n191: - Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n192: - AgentRuntimeClient has simpler lifecycle than CodeInterpreterClient (no control plane session management)\n193: - The `invoke` method is the primary way to interact with Agent Runtime\n194: - Use the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n195: - Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027\n\n(End of file - total 195 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775870153856,"end":1775870153863}}}}
